- ## keybinds:
	- `F` - video formats toggle
	- `t` - seek to the timestamp you type
	- `HOME` - previous chapter
	- `END` - next chapter
	- `o/P` - show proggression bar
	- `left-right arrow` - seek 5sec forward/backward
	- `up-down arrow` - seek forward/backward 1 minute
	- `scroll wheel` - scroll thrrough the video seek
	- `[/]` - increase playback speed
	- `{/}` - halve/double playback speed
	- `backspace` - reset playback speed
	- `//*` - inc/dec volume
	- `9/0` - inc/dec volume
	- `m` - mute
	- `enter` - go forward in the playlist
	- `p/space` - pause
	- `q` - quit
	- `f` - fullscreen
	- `O` - toggle OSD states between normal and playback time/duratio
	- `s` - take screenshot
	- `v` - toggle subtitles
	- `z/Z` - adjust subtitle delay
	- `Shift + g/Shift + f` - adjust subtitle size
	- `C-+/C--` - adjust audio delay
	- `,/.` - step forward/backward (1 klatke do przodu/ty≈Çu)
	- `Q` - like `q` but store the current playback position
	- `_` - disable/enable video output
	- `#` - disable/enable audio foutput
- ## keybinds from scripts
	- ### crop.lua
		- `c` - start-crop and full screen
		- `alt-c` - start-crop and not full screen
		- `l` - start-blur blur/delogo something
		- `d` - remove video filters (blur/delogo)
		- `0` - remove the zoom
		- uses config - crop.conf
	- ### encode.lua
		- `e` - encode, set the beginning of the extract, press enter to set the end and sstart encoding (use default profile)
		- `E` - use custom webm profle - encode_webm.conf
	- ### seek-to.lua
		- `t` - seek to the timestamp you type
		- `enter` - seek to the entered position
		- move the current position with `right-arrow` and `left-arrow`
		- scroll through history of timestamps that have been previous nagivated with `up-arrow` and `down-arrow`
	- ### blur-edges.lua
		- `b` - toggle blur-edges
		- uses config - blur_edges.conf
	- ### quality-menu.lua
		- `F` - video formats toggle
		- `Alt-f` - audio formats toggle
		- `Ctrl-r` - restarts quality menu
	- ### total_playtime.lua
		- `T` - shows total playtime of current playlist
		- `alt+d` - sorts playlist by duration. Repeated keypress reverses the order
		- `shift+alt+d` - sorts playlist by duration and jumps to the first entry. Repeated keypress reverses the order
	- ### betterchapters.lua
		- `HOME` - previous chapter
		- `END` - next chapter
- ## scripts without keybinds
	- ### blacklist-extensions.lua
		- automatically remove playlist entries by extensions according to a black/whitelist. Usefull when opening directories with mpv (e.g. when u do `mpv *`)
		- uses profile - blacklist_extension.conf
	- ### misc.lua
		- the generall appearance script - don't touch
	- ### speed_os3.lua
		- shows the time till end when sped up
	- ### modern.lua
		- upgrade mpv appearance

